---
const withBase = (path: string) => {
  const base = '/arcup';
  if (path === '/') return `${base}/`;
  return `${base}${path}`;
};
---

<main id="main-content" class="page-shell page-why-clean" aria-labelledby="why-title">
  
  <!-- ==================== HERO ==================== -->
  <header class="why-hero-clean" aria-labelledby="why-title">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">the answer to "why we need arc^"</p>
    <h1 id="why-title" class="hero-question">
      what if the next big breakthrough<br />was built in the open?
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-subquestion">
      in that world, what future would your novel idea create?
    </p>
    <p class="hero-origin">
      arc^ began from that question. not as a product idea, but from a moment of reflection.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 1: THE PROBLEM ==================== -->
  <section class="section-problem-clean" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="problem-heading" class="section-title">what's the problem?</h2>

      <div class="problem-questions">
        <p class="question-italic">if i follow the same path as the past</p>
        <p class="question-italic">and if everyone does the same</p>
        <p class="question-italic">will we ever reach the futures we hope for?</p>
      </div>

      <p class="narrative-lead">i looked backward and saw a pattern:</p>

      <!-- Simple Linear Pattern -->
      <div class="pattern-simple">
        <span class="pattern-word">conflict</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow">→</span>
        <span class="pattern-word">production</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow">→</span>
        <span class="pattern-word">patents</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow">→</span>
        <span class="pattern-word">profit</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow">→</span>
        <span class="pattern-word">power</span>
        <span class="pattern-arrow pattern-arrow-harm">→</span>
        <span class="pattern-word pattern-word-harm">harm</span>
      </div>

      <p class="pattern-caption">
        a repeating cycle of violence, materialism, and extraction. dressed up as progress.
      </p>

      <!-- Today's Loop -->
      <div class="today-block">
        <p class="today-label">today that loop looks like:</p>
        <ul class="today-list">
          <li>curiosity gated by funding.</li>
          <li>discovery delayed for the market.</li>
          <li>scale that replaces meaning.</li>
          <li>top-down incentives overriding truths of practice.</li>
          <li>science run as strategy, not as a humble search for knowledge.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- The Cost Block - T-SHAPED LAYOUT -->
      <div class="cost-block-t-shape">
        <div class="t-shape-top">
          <div class="t-left">
            <p class="consequence-text">
              our best ideas are dying waiting for approval from systems that no longer serve us.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="t-right">
            <p class="wait-line">we wait.</p>
            <p class="wait-line">we delay.</p>
            <p class="wait-line">we privatize.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="t-bottom">
          <p class="cost-text">
            and it <strong>has cost us dearly:</strong> exploited people, collapsing ecosystems, fractured communities, polarisation, and futures that are becoming harder to inherit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Refusal -->
      <div class="refusal-block">
        <p class="refusal-statement">
          arc^ refuses to copy/paste the old playbook.<br />
          it doesn't work. it won't get us where we must go.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- IF WE SUCCEED - MOVED HERE -->
      <div class="success-vision">
        <h3>if we succeed</h3>
        <p>
          We'll host a public library of community solutions hardware blueprints, protocols, templates and a set of tested case studies that let local projects replicate and adapt without gatekeepers.
        </p>
        <p class="success-goal">
          <strong>Our biggest goal:</strong> shift our relationship with technology so that it supports humanity's repair and flourishing.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 2: THE APPROACH ==================== -->
  <section class="section-approach-clean" aria-labelledby="approach-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="approach-heading" class="section-title">what's the approach?</h2>

      <div class="approach-questions">
        <p class="question-italic">what if the most ambitious goals our most outlandish visions were grounded in accountability?</p>
        <p class="question-italic">what if responsibility not secrecy, not profit defined innovation?</p>
      </div>

      <div class="approach-definition-block">
        <p>
          arc^ is not a brand. It's not a product. It's not a lab that will magically "save the world."
        </p>
        <p class="definition-emphasis">
          <strong>arc^ is a decision about how we want to be human together:</strong> science as philosophy, praxis and partnership.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="approach-text-block">
        <p>
          We choose to build in the open, because outdated frameworks that protect work by locking it away are causing harm. 
          Accountability becomes the architecture of that choice: obligations that are visible, measurable, and reproducible.
        </p>
        <p>
          We design with repair in mind. We are responsible to collective goals the goals of the many and we measure everything by their consequences on people, ecosystems, and future generations. 
          We operate to minimize harm and maximize repair.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- RE:TECH -->
      <div class="retech-block">
        <h3>RE:TECH our design posture</h3>
        <p class="retech-tagline">Refuse Extractive Technology.</p>
        <p class="retech-description">
          If a tool, process, or system extracts, exploits, or restricts repair and restoration we do not build it.
        </p>

        <div class="retech-grid">
          <div class="retech-item">
            <h4>transparent</h4>
            <p>not hidden behind NDAs and patents</p>
          </div>
          <div class="retech-item">
            <h4>collaborative</h4>
            <p>not competitive and extractive</p>
          </div>
          <div class="retech-item">
            <h4>regenerative</h4>
            <p>not extractive and destructive</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Accountability -->
      <div class="accountability-block">
        <p class="block-label">what responsibility looks like here:</p>
        <ul class="accountability-list">
          <li>Public protocols published from day 0.</li>
          <li>Named stewards who are accountable for projects.</li>
          <li>Consent and co-design with affected communities.</li>
          <li>Reproducibility tests, audits, and public impact reports.</li>
          <li>Ethics gates that must be passed before anything scales.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="accountability-close">
          Accountability is not an add-on. It's how arc^ operates.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="section-cta">
        <a href="#retech-docs" class="cta-link">Learn more about the RE:TECH framework →</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 3: WHAT WE BUILD ==================== -->
  <section class="section-build-clean" aria-labelledby="build-heading">
    <div class="section-container">
      
      <h2 id="build-heading" class="section-title">what do we build?</h2>

      <div class="build-intro-block">
        <h3 class="build-subtitle">open infrastructure for collective repair.</h3>
        <p>
          arc^ builds the tools, protocols, templates, and living prototypes that let ambitious science happen in public without exploiting people or the planet. We want discovery to belong to many, not to a privileged few, and to make sure scale is bound to consent and repair.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Living Work -->
      <div class="content-block">
        <h4>living, growing, evolving products not polished patented barriers</h4>
        <p>
          We publish early and deliberately: prototypes, experiment notebooks, versioned protocols, modular components that others can adopt, test, and extend. Our goal is reproducible momentum, not a private patent that sits on a shelf.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Core Goals -->
      <div class="content-block">
        <h4>core goals</h4>
        <ul class="goals-list">
          <li>Rebuild safe, open plasma technologies: modular, documented, replicable.</li>
          <li>Release hardware blueprints and DBD / reactor components as community assets.</li>
          <li>Create a public library ArcIndex of open protocols, templates, and community solutions.</li>
          <li>Produce governance templates and consent frameworks for community-led research.</li>
          <li>Help regenerative, local solutions scale ethically not extractively.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Research Areas -->
      <div class="research-block">
        <h4>research areas</h4>
        <div class="research-grid-clean">
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Open Plasma Systems</h5>
            <p>Modular plasma-reactor designs, safety-first, reproducible in community labs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>DBD Components & Hardware</h5>
            <p>Open blueprints for dielectric-barrier discharge components and build guides.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Salt & Water Systems</h5>
            <p>Research on low-cost, regenerative irrigation and saline-adapted solutions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Remediation & Restoration</h5>
            <p>Protocols for soil, water, and air remediation using scalable, community-deployable tech.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Human & Environmental Health</h5>
            <p>Open studies focused on measurable, community-centered health outcomes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="research-item">
            <h5>Reproducibility Tooling</h5>
            <p>Tests, CI scripts, and notebooks to make experiments repeatable by anyone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="section-cta">
        <a href="#join" class="cta-link">Get involved →</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== CLOSING ==================== -->
  <section class="closing-clean">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p class="closing-statement">
        arc^ builds <strong>open infrastructure for collective repair</strong> 
        tools, knowledge, and networks that reject the extractive paradigm.
      </p>
      <p class="closing-emphasis">
        because the systems that got us here <strong>won't get us out</strong>.
      </p>

      <div class="closing-ctas">
        <a href={withBase('/join')} class="button button-primary">Join Us</a>
        <a href={withBase('/how')} class="button button-secondary">Explore How</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>
